letter and the letter’s legacy of hierarchy and obedience. The volume concludes with four essays on the way in which the letter was interpreted by the some of the Church Fathers: Origen, Jerome, Chrystostom, Augustine and Theodore of Mopsuestia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aEpistolographie. 4aExegese. 4aKirchenväter. 4aNeues Testament. 4aPaulinische Literatur. 4aPhilemonbrief. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / New Testament.2bisacsh  aChurch Fathers.  aLetter to Philemon.  aNew Testament.  aPauline Literature.1 aArtz-Grabner, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAtkins, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBotha, Pieter J. J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDecock, Paul B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFitzgerald, John T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedl, Alfred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLampe, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPunt, Jeremy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTolmie, D. Francois, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTolmie,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVilliers, Pieter G. R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeima, Jefferey A. D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWendland, Ernst, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWessels, G. Francois, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWet, Chris L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWolte